channel.title: Foods
channel.description:
I got a question for moparscape. [size=1pt]*cough* elveage *cough*[/size]
What is your daily diet? I'm not talking about how you stay fit, just what do you normally (as in you don't realize it, subconsciously) eat as part of your routine during the day?
Mine usually consists of two egg, ham, cheese sandwiches or a bowl of cereal/soup for breakfast. Chicken sandwich (My school sucks, kay?) for lunch, and whatever is in my kitchen for dinner.

item.title: Foods
item.dc:creator: @Cole1497 Cole1497
item.description:
@Cole1497 wrote:

Breakfast: Sometimes a doughnut, though hardly ever
Lunch: A bottle of water and Mike and Ikes
Dinner: Usually nothing

I think this is really bad for my health, as this is what I have 4 days a week.
Douchebag band teacher lets us out 5 minutes late, after we’ve told him about it, and by the time I get to the cafeteria there’s nothing left except corn.
So I go to a vending machine, get mike and ikes, water, and that’s my lunch.
My mom is both pregnant and sick, so she can’t really make my dinner. Occasionally I’ll just make Ramen.

Srry 4 lief story
